<p>How do I overload the '&lt;' (less than) operator for pair of ints to insert the elements of this type into set. For example, consider the following program</p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; #include &lt;utility&gt; #include &lt;set&gt; using namespace std;  bool operator&lt;(pair&lt;int, int&gt; a, pair&lt;int, int&gt; b){   if(a.second &lt; b.second) return true;   if(a.second == b.second) return a.first &lt; b.first;   return false; }  int main(){   pair&lt;int, int&gt; a = make_pair(1, 4);   pair&lt;int, int&gt; b = make_pair(2, 3);   set&lt;pair&lt;int ,int&gt; &gt; s;   s.insert(b);   s.insert(a);   set&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt; &gt;::iterator it = s.begin();   for(; it!=s.end(); it++){     printf("(%d %d)\n", it-&gt;first, it-&gt;second);   }   if(a &lt; b) printf("a &lt; b\n");   else printf("b &lt; a\n"); } </code></pre>  <p>The output produced by the above code is:</p>  <pre><code>(1 4) (2 3) b &lt; a </code></pre>  <p>I want the elements of the set to be ordered by the second element of the pair structure. How to do this?</p>